begin_memory_text: We talked about where we were from and what colleges we went to and other general background information. I found out he was from Oregon, born and raised, and went to the University of Oregon.
middle_memory_text: We discussed past experiences with children and him wanting to teach children in the past, but not anymore. We also talked about our pets and his wife.
end_memory_text: We talked about music tastes and what our favorite bands were. We also talked about one direction, and I shared a story about it.
rest_of_day_open: I see it going pretty well. I have a lot of stuff to get done and pick up before I go to see my boyfriend for a long period of time. I think this week will be a good week for me. I am excited to do my workouts this week.
critical_positive: Though there were awkward pauses, my partner was better at carrying on a conversation and making it flow through those pauses. We were both on the quieter side, which I think was a positive because both of us were conscious of giving the other person time to speak. It was comfortable.
critical_negative: Occasionally there were moments were the conversation kind of abruptly died, through no fault of either party. It's normal to have lulls in a conversation, but for some reason those moments still feel a little awkward. I was a tad bit shy, which could have made it harder for the conversation to get rolling.

begin_memory_text: At the beginning of the conversation we talked about where we lived and kinda what we are doing. She lives in LA currently but was from chicago
middle_memory_text: We talked about different things that we enjoyed like traveling and the places that she would want to go. She was interested in visiting france or south korea.
end_memory_text: At the end we talked about different music that we liked. She was a very big one direction fan and then I talked about how my wife was a big fan of them too.
rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of the week going well for me personally, but several members of my family are sick right now. So I am worried that they are doing okay. I plan on cooking some really good meals coming up this week to help with my wifes recovery. It may not help her physically but it will emotionally.
critical_positive: The conversation went very well, but I know I was slightly nervous so the conversation could have smoother. I thought I did a good job asking question and keeping my partner engaged. I slipped up speaking quite a few times, just stammering because of my nerves. I really enjoyed the topics we discussed though.
critical_negative: I stammered quit a bit when talking to her, but I tried to compensate for this by being very friendly and engaging. There wasnt too many other things that went poorly. I wish I could have spoken clearer and focused on looking at the camera so i could connect better with my partner.
